@startuml
title Incoming DICOM & RTSTRUCT Handling Sequence
autonumber

participant "External Modality
(CT/TPS)" as Ext
participant "DicomListener" as Listener
participant "FileSystemManager" as FSM
participant "Local Storage" as Disk
participant "Watchdog
Observer" as Watchdog

== Association Negotiation ==
Ext -> Listener: A-ASSOCIATE-RQ
Listener -> Listener: Validate AE Title & IP
Listener --> Ext: A-ASSOCIATE-AC

== File Transfer Loop ==
loop For each DICOM file in study
    Ext -> Listener: C-STORE-RQ (Dataset)
    activate Listener
    
    Listener -> FSM: save_incoming_dicom(dataset, meta)
    activate FSM
    
    FSM -> FSM: Extract StudyInstanceUID
    FSM -> FSM: Extract SOPClassUID / Modality
    
    alt is RTSTRUCT (1.2.840...481.3)
        FSM -> Disk: Write to .../UID_<uid>/Structure/<sop_uid>.dcm
        note right: Segregates RT Structure Sets
    else Standard DICOM (CT/MR/etc)
        FSM -> Disk: Write to .../UID_<uid>/DCM/<sop_uid>.dcm
        note right: Standard Image Storage
    end
    
    FSM --> Listener: return file_path
    deactivate FSM
    
    Listener --> Ext: C-STORE-RSP (Success: 0x0000)
    
    par Async Watchdog Event
        Disk -> Watchdog: File Created/Modified Event
        activate Watchdog
        Watchdog -> Watchdog: _start_debounce_timer(study_path)
        note right: Resets debounce timer.
Prevents premature processing.
        deactivate Watchdog
    end
    
    deactivate Listener
end

== Association Release ==
Ext -> Listener: A-RELEASE-RQ
Listener --> Ext: A-RELEASE-RP
Listener -> Listener: _handle_conn_close
note over Listener, Watchdog: Connection closed. System waits for Watchdog timer
to expire (no new files) before triggering StudyProcessor.

@enduml
